<font color="#FF0000">JUST  A THOUGHT</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jan 30 19:48:35 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Where do I start? So long ago, yet fresh in my mind. It does not matter who I am, what outfit I was in. How many I killed. What matters is I was there. I stared death in the eyes, I managed to beat it. Sadly enough sometimes I regret it. Many friends did not come back. I may be ridden with guilt. I saw agony in children, mothers scrounging for food and elderly men and women whom had ever eaten an apple. I saw beauty destroyed, heard bombs whistling by. I came back. We did what we were trained to do, are we guilty? I fear and hate the night, the loud noise or the child that cries. The grunt I knew, the ones I never knew. The pictures I took of the people and their land. Can I cope with the guilt? Is it guilt? Can I cry or should I remain silent? Only God knows! Maybe! I lost innocence and much much more. All my vet friends lost that too. I hardly have friends its hard to have them you think you'll lose them. It's hard to trust. Thank God, I now have a wife that understands, maybe. She cares and has a constant vigil over me. Perhaps this is why I was permitted to return, so I could teach my children the resulting horrors of any war. Though I will state for the record, I would do it again, fight a thousand wars, anywhere any time, against any enemy, face death again so my children can be spared the loosing their innocence. I better stop, maybe I'll write again. I pray I can be at peace someday.<br>
                                     THANKS 
